Reasoning: The paper deals with analyzing the performance of a multi-cell downlink system with base station cooperation using regularized zero-forcing precoding. This involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), mathematical analysis (cs.MA), and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of random matrix theory and optimization techniques further supports these categories.
